**Production:** Lo-fi aesthetic, tape saturation, often recorded with a vintage, slightly warbly quality. The Rocky Road/Leslie pedal in the mix creates that vintage psychedelic studio feel even on live-leaning recordings.

**Chord approach:** Babe Rainbow lean heavily into major key progressions with 60s pop sensibility — think I-IV-V with added major 7ths and open-tuning voicings. Their softer, folksier approach means they often use first-position chords with open strings rather than barre chord up the neck. The wah adds mid-frequency movement to static chord progressions.

**Key tracks:** Their "Naturally" and "Good To Be Alive" era material shows the full toolkit. Available on their Bandcamp (baberainbow.bandcamp.com). Chord tabs sparse online — best approach is to listen for the I-bVII-IV movement in their major key songs.

